[ Both Laughing ]

01:17.977 --> 01:20.969
[ Laughing ]
''Web site.''

01:21.081 --> 01:24.107
- [ Man ] Okay, here's another news ''flush.''
- [ Toilet Flushing ]

01:24.217 --> 01:26.447
## [ Man Singing ]

01:26.553 --> 01:31.581
<i>Doctors say the life expectancy
of the average man is now 76.2 years.</i>

01:31.691 --> 01:33.591
[ Gasps ]

01:33.693 --> 01:35.888
- [ Tires Screeching ]
- [ Horns Honking ]

01:35.995 --> 01:40.056
7 6.2? But I'm already 38.1 .

01:40.166 --> 01:42.361
I've wasted half my life.

01:42.469 --> 01:43.993
## [ Man Singing ]

01:44.104 --> 01:48.234
Half my life gone and I'm only guaranteed
38 more years.

01:48.341 --> 01:50.969
[ Horns Honking ]

01:52.212 --> 01:55.045
Marge, I've wasted half my life.

01:55.148 --> 01:57.048
[ Woman ]
Sir, do you need a tow truck?

01:57.150 --> 02:00.517
<i>- What are you talking about, Marge?
I don't need a-
- [ Tires Screeching ]</i>

02:00.620 --> 02:02.520
Okay, send a truck.

02:03.957 --> 02:07.586
<i>- Oh. Hmm.
- [ Marge ] Oh, honey. Don't eat that.</i>

02:07.694 --> 02:09.821
Wouldn't you rather have
your sugar bag?

02:09.929 --> 02:11.897
No, I don't deserve sugar.

02:11.998 --> 02:15.490
I'm halfway to my grave,
and I haven't accomplished anything.

02:15.602 --> 02:19.698
Oh, I am not looking forward
to my funeral.

02:19.806 --> 02:22.036
[ Electricity Buzzing ]

02:24.077 --> 02:25.977
[ Beeping ]

02:27.046 --> 02:30.413
<i>No, Homer wasn't a great man...</i>

02:30.517 --> 02:34.578
nor even an adequate man,
and he certainly never accomplished anything.

02:34.687 --> 02:37.349
Uh, President Lenny,
you have anything to say?

02:37.457 --> 02:40.426
- Nah.
- All right. Fair enough. Toss 'im in the hole, boys.

02:42.829 --> 02:45.662
There goes a real sack of crap.

02:45.765 --> 02:48.199
Indubitably, old chum.

02:49.702 --> 02:51.169
[ Growling ]

02:51.271 --> 02:53.330
[ Groans ]
Marge...

02:53.439 --> 02:56.306
no matter what happens in the future,
promise me you won't vote for Lenny.

02:56.409 --> 02:58.343
Okay, but you've accomplished a lot.

02:58.444 --> 03:00.571
You've made me very happy.

03:00.680 --> 03:02.910
Oh, yeah. They'll put me
on a stamp for that.

03:03.016 --> 03:06.042
- [ Groans ]
- I've wasted half my life, Marge.

03:06.152 --> 03:09.121
You know how many memories
I have? Three!

03:09.222 --> 03:11.122
Standing in line for a movie...

03:11.224 --> 03:14.022
having a key made
and sitting here talking to you.

03:14.127 --> 03:17.153
Thirty-eight years
and that's all I have to show for it.

03:17.263 --> 03:19.891
- You're 39.
- [ Yelps ]

03:19.999 --> 03:22.024
[ Whimpers ]

03:28.107 --> 03:30.598
[ Groans ]

03:30.710 --> 03:33.406
- Hi, Dad. How was work?
- Cold.

03:33.513 --> 03:36.004
Come on. Let's get you
into your favorite shirt.

03:37.884 --> 03:39.977
[ All ]
Surprise!

03:40.086 --> 03:43.886
Oh. I see you're having a party.
I'll come back later.

03:43.990 --> 03:46.458
You can't come back later because-

03:46.559 --> 03:49.153
[ All ] Homer Simpson,
welcome to your life.

03:49.262 --> 03:51.162
...to your life.

03:53.933 --> 03:57.198
The kids and I wanna
show you all the great things you've done.

03:57.303 --> 04:00.534
Oh, all right. Maybe I can pinpoint
where my life went wrong.

04:00.640 --> 04:02.835
Quiet, Dad, or we'll
have to throw you out of here.

04:02.942 --> 04:07.003
[ Gasps ] The pictures!
They're coming alive!

04:07.113 --> 04:10.207
<i>[ Lisa ] There you are in outer space.
That's pretty impressive.</i>

04:10.316 --> 04:14.980
Ah. All we did was grow some space tomatoes
and sabotage Mir.

04:17.890 --> 04:19.414
[ Shouting In Russian ]

04:19.524 --> 04:21.891
'Member when you almost
became heavyweight champ?

04:21.995 --> 04:24.156
[ Crowd Cheering ]

04:26.399 --> 04:28.833
<i>- [ Blows Landing ]
- No.</i>

04:28.935 --> 04:30.835
Finish him. Finish him!

04:30.937 --> 04:33.428
Well, there's certainly
no greater accomplishment...

04:33.539 --> 04:36.303
than fathering
three beautiful children.

04:36.409 --> 04:38.309
Hike.

04:39.479 --> 04:41.379
[ Laughing ]

04:41.481 --> 04:44.678
Oh, I should've punted.
Turn it off. Turn it off.

04:44.784 --> 04:47.947
Hang on, Dad. This next part will definitely
make you feel better about yourself.

04:49.889 --> 04:54.656
<i>- Hello, Homer. It's me, KITT,
from TV's Knight Rider.
- [ Gasps ]</i>

04:54.761 --> 04:56.729
Your family has asked me
to take time out...

04:56.829 --> 04:58.729
from my busy schedule
to invite you...

04:58.831 --> 05:02.824
[ Voice Slowing Down ]
to a very special- [ Indistinct ]

05:04.737 --> 05:07.501
[ Groaning ]
Stupid movies.

05:07.607 --> 05:11.134
Who invented these dumb things anyway?
Was it you, Bart?

05:11.244 --> 05:14.475
- It was Thomas Edison, Dad.
- I thought he invented the lightbulb.

05:14.580 --> 05:18.516
That too. He also invented the phonograph,
the microphone and the electric car.

05:18.618 --> 05:20.518
No one man can do all that.

05:20.620 --> 05:22.520
You're a liar, honey-
a dirty, rotten liar.

05:22.622 --> 05:24.556
Finish her! Finish her!

05:24.657 --> 05:27.854
It's true. I read it
on a place mat at a restaurant.

05:27.960 --> 05:32.397
Really? A restaurant?
Well, now I don't know what to think.

05:32.498 --> 05:32.598
<i>Go.! Go.! Go.!</i>

05:32.598 --> 05:34.896
<i>Go.! Go.! Go.!</i>

05:35.001 --> 05:38.027
- Go! Go! Go!
- Top of the world, Ma!

05:38.137 --> 05:41.038
<i>- [ Homer ] Cut it out, boy.
- [ Screams, Grunts ]</i>

05:42.709 --> 05:45.906
- Dad, what are you doin' here?
- Readin' about this Edison character.

05:46.012 --> 05:48.640
They won't let me
in the big people library downtown.

05:48.748 --> 05:52.684
There was some... unpleasantness.
I can never go back.

05:52.785 --> 05:56.312
Ooh. Look at all the inventions
Edison came up with.

05:56.422 --> 05:58.515
The stock ticker...

05:58.624 --> 06:00.524
the storage battery...

06:00.626 --> 06:02.526
even wax paper.

06:02.628 --> 06:04.892
And look at him dance.
## [ Vocalizing ]

06:04.997 --> 06:07.158
[ Laughing ]

06:08.334 --> 06:10.234
That's great, Dad.

06:10.336 --> 06:12.270
And these Hardy Boys books
are great too.

06:12.372 --> 06:14.772
- This one's about smugglers.
- They're all about smugglers.

06:14.874 --> 06:18.776
<i>No, not this one: The Smugglers of Pirate Cove.
It's about pirates.</i>

06:18.878 --> 06:21.642
'Scuse me. Are you
a student at this school?

06:21.748 --> 06:24.774
I think it's pretty obvious
that I am.

06:24.884 --> 06:26.818
Go school!

06:27.987 --> 06:31.184
<i>So, this broad
stands up in the ocean...</i>

06:31.290 --> 06:34.282
and this big wave
knocks her bathing suit off.

06:34.394 --> 06:36.419
Oh, yeah? And then what happened?

06:36.529 --> 06:39.054
Omit no detail,
however small or filthy.

06:39.165 --> 06:43.465
So anyway, and this is the part
you'll remember for the rest of your lives-

06:43.569 --> 06:45.469
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.
Great story, Lenny.

06:45.571 --> 06:48.096
But here's one
that's even more spellbinding.

06:48.207 --> 06:52.541
Once upon a time,
there was a man named Thomas Edison...

06:52.645 --> 06:56.877
and he invented
the dictating machine and the fluoroscope...

06:56.983 --> 06:59.417
and the repeating telegraph.

06:59.519 --> 07:01.419
- [ Snoring ]
- And he was a firm believer in Fletcherism...

07:01.521 --> 07:04.251
and he played the organ
and his favorite flower was the heliotrope.

07:04.357 --> 07:06.257
Oh, and his middle name was Alva...

07:06.359 --> 07:09.260
<i>and he never, ever,
ever wore pajamas.</i>

07:09.362 --> 07:11.887
Okay. I think we've been polite
long enough here.

07:11.998 --> 07:14.728
- Lenny, what happened with
the dame in the bathing suit?
- Huh?

07:14.834 --> 07:17.234
Oh. Uh-

07:17.336 --> 07:19.827
Oh, nuts. I forgot.

07:19.939 --> 07:23.033
All I can think of now is Edison.
I can't even remember where I work.

07:23.142 --> 07:26.134
Well, I remember where Edison worked.
It was Menlo Park.

07:26.245 --> 07:29.146
That's where he came up with the tasimeter,
the ore separator and-

07:29.248 --> 07:32.081
Uh,James Watt
invented the steam engine.

07:32.185 --> 07:34.653
That's boring.
You're boring everybody.

07:34.754 --> 07:36.654
Quit boring everyone!

07:36.756 --> 07:39.350
<i>And then he worked on a machine
to communicate with the dead.</i>

07:39.459 --> 07:41.359
- [ Groans ]
- Some kind of scary telephone, I guess.

07:41.461 --> 07:44.726
- Maybe he planned to stick his
head under the ground and yell.
- All right already!

07:44.831 --> 07:46.992
Everyone knows
the man accomplished a lot.

07:47.099 --> 07:51.126
Maybe because he didn't spend every
waking moment talking about Thomas Edison.

07:51.237 --> 07:53.137
Oh, that's where
you're wrong, Marge.

07:53.239 --> 07:55.605
He was a shameless self-promoter.

07:55.708 --> 07:58.404
Well, you're not Thomas Edison.

07:58.511 --> 08:02.572
Marge, that's it!
That's why I haven't done anything with my life.

08:02.682 --> 08:05.480
I need to be
more like Thomas Edison.

08:05.585 --> 08:07.485
Whatever.

08:07.587 --> 08:09.555
And I'm starting right now.

08:09.655 --> 08:12.818
No more lousy pajamas!
[ Grunts ]

08:12.925 --> 08:15.826
From this day forward,
I am an inventor!

08:16.996 --> 08:20.432
Do us a favor.
Invent yourself some underpants.

08:25.238 --> 08:28.105
## [ Whistling ]

08:28.207 --> 08:30.368
Ah.

08:30.476 --> 08:33.070
Well, I quit my job
just like you said to.

08:33.179 --> 08:35.374
I didn't tell you to quit your job.

08:35.481 --> 08:37.972
Yes, you did.
I remember your exact words.

08:38.083 --> 08:42.851
You said I should quit my job and become
an inventor, or you'd torch the house.

08:42.955 --> 08:45.788
That doesn't sound like me.

08:45.892 --> 08:49.828
Well, I suppose if this doesn't work out,
you can always go back to the plant.

08:49.929 --> 08:53.865
[ Chuckling ]
Not the way I quit.

08:53.966 --> 08:56.230
Whoo-hoo.

09:07.446 --> 09:11.883
At my age, Edison
had already invented 203 things.

09:11.984 --> 09:15.545
Uh, I got a lot of work to do
to catch up to him.

09:15.655 --> 09:20.058
Let's see now. Invention. Invention.

09:22.128 --> 09:25.154
Hmm. Hmm.

09:25.264 --> 09:27.255
Something electrical might be good.

09:27.366 --> 09:30.301
[ Muttering ]
Let me handle the creative end of this, Marge.

09:30.403 --> 09:34.533
- You don't understand how the
creative mind works like I do.
- Oh?

09:34.640 --> 09:38.633
You look at this table
and what do you see? Just a table.

09:38.744 --> 09:40.769
Now a creative person like me
looks at this table...

09:40.880 --> 09:44.782
and sees all kinds
of creative things, but no tables.

09:44.884 --> 09:47.478
Homer, that's not a table.
That's our dryer.

09:47.587 --> 09:50.317
[ Shrieks ]
My files!

09:50.423 --> 09:52.254
Hmm.

09:54.560 --> 09:58.553
Hmm. This isn't working.
I've gotta try a different approach.

09:58.664 --> 10:01.292
Hmm. Hmm?

10:01.400 --> 10:04.267
Hmm? Hmm?

10:07.540 --> 10:10.202
[ Grunts, Gasps ]

10:10.309 --> 10:12.038
[ Groans ]

10:14.847 --> 10:16.781
[ Coughing ]

10:17.917 --> 10:21.216
[ Sighs, Coughs ]

10:21.320 --> 10:23.220
You started smoking, Dad?

10:23.322 --> 10:26.621
Yes. Thomas Edison
smoked several cigars a day.

10:26.726 --> 10:28.660
- Yeah, he invented stuff too.
- Shut up.

10:30.262 --> 10:32.162
[ Grunting, Shouts ]

10:34.000 --> 10:36.764
As long as you're here annoying me,
let's have a brainstorming session.

10:36.869 --> 10:41.067
And here's how it works. Lisa, you say
one thing, then Bart, you say another.

10:41.173 --> 10:43.198
Just toss out things and
I'll use my inventive mind...

10:43.309 --> 10:46.176
to combine them
into a brilliant, original idea.

10:46.278 --> 10:48.178
Okay. Um-

10:48.280 --> 10:50.180
- Automatic-
- Butt.

10:50.282 --> 10:51.806
Okay.

10:51.917 --> 10:55.580
- Fluorescent-
- Booger.

10:55.688 --> 10:57.588
Mm-hmm. Yeah.

10:57.690 --> 11:01.421
Wait a minute. These aren't exciting new products.
You're not even trying.

11:01.527 --> 11:04.690
Okay, that's it. Both of you
go to your rooms and spank yourselves.

11:07.900 --> 11:12.166
- Lazy father.
- Can't even spank his own kids.

11:12.271 --> 11:17.299
Homer, you can't punish the children
just because you can't come up with an idea.

11:17.410 --> 11:21.005
- I don't see why not. They're my kids. I own 'em.
- [ Groans ]

11:21.113 --> 11:24.480
<i>- Okay. We own 'em.
- Hmm.</i>

11:24.583 --> 11:28.417
I brought you a tuna sandwich.
They say it's brain food.

11:28.521 --> 11:30.546
I guess because
there's so much dolphin in it...

11:30.656 --> 11:32.590
<i>and you know how smart they are.</i>

11:32.692 --> 11:34.592
[ Groans ]
It's no use.

11:34.694 --> 11:37.720
I can't work like this,
cut off from the scientific community.

11:39.298 --> 11:41.823
You stay here and guard my sandwich.

11:41.934 --> 11:45.495
<i>And these should give you
the grounding you'll need...</i>

11:45.604 --> 11:49.165
in thermodynamics,
hypermathematics...

11:49.275 --> 11:52.608
and, of course, microcalifragilistics.
[ Babbles ]

11:52.712 --> 11:57.342
[ Groans ] Look, I just wanna know
how to invent things. Tell me.

11:57.450 --> 12:01.318
Uh, all you have to do
is think of things that people need...

12:01.420 --> 12:03.320
but which don't exist yet.

12:03.422 --> 12:07.756
- You mean like an electric blanket-mobile?
- Uh, well, possibl-

12:07.860 --> 12:12.559
Or you could take something that already exists
and find a new use for it. Like-

12:12.665 --> 12:14.599
Hamburger earmuffs!

12:14.700 --> 12:18.295
Uh, well, I suppose
that would qualify-

12:18.404 --> 12:20.304
Thanks, sucker!

12:20.406 --> 12:24.604
[ Stammering ]
All right.Just stay calm, Frinky.

12:24.710 --> 12:26.610
These babies
will be in the stores...

12:26.712 --> 12:28.612
while he's still grappling
with the pickle matrix.

12:28.714 --> 12:30.682
[ Babbling ]

12:40.693 --> 12:42.388
[ Explosion ]

12:58.778 --> 13:01.906
Okay. I have here
the four greatest inventions...

13:02.014 --> 13:05.381
in the history of mankind.

13:06.552 --> 13:09.680
First, my all-purpose
electric hammer...

13:09.789 --> 13:12.087
for all your pounding needs.

13:13.759 --> 13:16.193
[ Grunting ]
Ow!

13:16.295 --> 13:18.820
- [ Muttering ]
- [ Screeches ]

13:18.931 --> 13:21.365
<i>- [ Crash ]
- [ Santa's Little Helper Barks ]</i>

13:21.467 --> 13:24.231
[ Yelping ]

13:24.336 --> 13:26.236
Probably needs to be more powerful.

13:26.338 --> 13:28.203
I'll buy 1 0 of those right now.

13:28.307 --> 13:31.834
Now, here's my
''Everything's Okay'' alarm.

13:31.944 --> 13:36.438
- [ Alarm Blaring ]
- [ Shouting ] This will sound every three seconds...

13:36.549 --> 13:39.313
unless something isn't okay.

13:39.418 --> 13:41.943
Turn that off, Homer.

13:42.054 --> 13:45.490
<i>- [ Alarm Continues ]
- It can't be turned off.</i>

13:45.591 --> 13:47.889
[ Alarm Slows, Stops ]

13:47.993 --> 13:49.961
But it, uh, does break easily.

13:50.062 --> 13:52.257
Now this next one's for the ladies.

13:52.364 --> 13:55.731
How many times have you gals been late
for a high-powered business meeting...

13:55.835 --> 13:58.770
only to realize
you're not wearing makeup?

13:58.871 --> 14:00.896
That's every woman's nightmare.

14:01.006 --> 14:04.066
That's why I invented
this revolutionary makeup gun.

14:04.176 --> 14:07.805
It's for the woman who only
has four-fifths of a second to get ready.

14:07.913 --> 14:10.848
Close your eyes, Marge.

14:10.950 --> 14:14.977
- And now you're ready for a night on the town.
- [ Gasps ]

14:15.087 --> 14:17.419
Homer, you've got it set on ''whore.''

14:17.523 --> 14:19.753
Uh, oop- Okay.

14:19.859 --> 14:22.726
This time, try to keep
your nostrils closed.

14:24.697 --> 14:28.189
Oh, look what you did.
Now I have to go get my cold cream gun.

14:28.300 --> 14:30.825
Dad, women won't like
being shot in the face.

14:30.936 --> 14:34.633
Women will like what I tell 'em to like.
Now here's something for everyone.

14:34.740 --> 14:38.836
In the olden times,
if you were watching TV and nature called...

14:38.944 --> 14:41.378
you'd have to get up
and walk to the bathroom.

14:41.480 --> 14:44.278
It was the hardest thing
in the world to do.

14:44.383 --> 14:48.251
But now, with the
Lazy Man Reclining Toilet Chair...

14:48.354 --> 14:51.152
you can just lean back
and let 'er rip.

14:51.257 --> 14:54.385
You expect people
to go to the bathroom in their living rooms?

14:54.493 --> 14:58.088
Sure. Believe me, every man in America
will want to have one.

14:58.197 --> 15:00.097
[ Flushes ]

15:00.199 --> 15:02.565
- Gangway! Gotta poop.
- No, Bart!

15:02.668 --> 15:07.105
- Homer, all these inventions, they're-
- Yes?

15:07.206 --> 15:10.198
- Oh-They're not very-
- Yes? Yes? Yes?

15:10.309 --> 15:12.174
- They're terrible.
- What?

15:12.278 --> 15:16.009
I'm not saying
you're a bad inventor.

15:16.115 --> 15:20.575
I'm just saying these particular... inventions
are awful...

15:20.686 --> 15:25.180
and no one in their right mind
would buy them or accept them as gifts.

15:25.291 --> 15:28.385
But this is the best I could do.

15:28.494 --> 15:32.760
I guess I'm no better at being Thomas Edison
than I was at being Homer Simpson.

15:35.467 --> 15:38.925
Oh, dear. I hope
I wasn't too rough on him.

15:39.038 --> 15:42.701
Somebody had to tell him, Mom.
In the long run, it's much kinder to-

15:42.808 --> 15:46.005
<i>[ Clears Throat ]
Do you mind?</i>

15:47.646 --> 15:52.242
All week, my lifelong dream was
to be the next Thomas Edison...

15:52.351 --> 15:54.251
but now it's over.

15:54.353 --> 15:57.015
I guess I'll just give up
my hopes and dreams...

15:57.122 --> 16:01.058
and settle for being
a decent husband and father. [ Grunting ]

16:01.160 --> 16:02.491
- Homer!
- [ Together] Dad!

16:02.594 --> 16:04.186
[ Shouts ]
Huh?

16:04.296 --> 16:07.959
- What happened? You didn't fall.
- Oh, that.

16:08.067 --> 16:09.967
I stuck a couple extra
legs on there...

16:10.069 --> 16:13.561
'cause I kept tipping over
when I was trying to invent stuff.

16:13.672 --> 16:16.300
They're on hinges.
That's really ingenious, Dad.

16:16.408 --> 16:20.105
- It could save lives.
- Really? You think it's a good idea?

16:20.212 --> 16:22.680
Oh, yeah. Safety sells,
especially to lame-o's.

16:22.781 --> 16:24.749
- I'd buy one.
- Me too.

16:24.850 --> 16:26.750
[ All Cooing ]

16:26.852 --> 16:28.786
I did it! I'm gonna be rich!

16:38.263 --> 16:41.130
## [ Humming ]

16:41.233 --> 16:44.430
Look, Mr. Edison.
I did it! I'm an inventor.

16:44.536 --> 16:47.369
And I owe it all to you.

16:47.473 --> 16:49.373
See? It's just a regular chair...

16:49.475 --> 16:51.670
but I attached
a couple of extra legs to the back...

16:51.777 --> 16:53.745
kind of like the ones
on the back of your-

16:55.414 --> 16:57.382
Oh, damn it!

16:57.483 --> 17:01.613
Hey, Dad. Heard you swearin'.
Mind if I join in? Crap, boobs, crap!

17:01.720 --> 17:04.119
I thought I had a great idea...

17:04.223 --> 17:07.386
but I must have seen it
on this poster.

17:07.492 --> 17:11.327
If Edison thought of that chair,
how come it's not on this chart?

17:11.430 --> 17:15.298
It's not? Maybe he never
told anyone about it.

17:15.401 --> 17:19.598
- That chair might be the only one he made.
- So?

17:19.704 --> 17:24.699
So, we've got to go to the Edison Museum
and smash it!

17:24.810 --> 17:27.175
Then I'll be an inventor.

17:27.279 --> 17:30.908
- But I thought you loved Edison.
- Ah, the hell with him.

17:31.016 --> 17:34.315
Yeah! Hell, damn, fart!

17:34.420 --> 17:38.083
<i>- [ Tires Screeching ]
- Taking Bart cross state lines. Back soon.</i>

17:39.158 --> 17:41.217
<i>I took your wallet.!</i>

17:41.326 --> 17:43.590
Oh, I just mopped that driveway.

17:47.399 --> 17:49.458
Man, I can't wait
to smash that chair.

17:49.568 --> 17:52.059
[ Chuckling ]
Oh, Son.

17:52.171 --> 17:55.572
You're young and headstrong
just like Thomas Edison Jr.

17:55.674 --> 17:59.132
You know, he started a mushroom farm
and an auto parts company...

17:59.244 --> 18:02.042
and he sold his good name
to a quack medicine company.

18:02.147 --> 18:05.548
Oh, and later he raised turkeys.
That was on his turkey farm.

18:05.651 --> 18:08.484
<i>[ Snoring ]</i>

18:11.523 --> 18:14.356
Hmm.

18:14.460 --> 18:17.122
Mmm. Mmm.

18:17.229 --> 18:21.393
[ Muttering, Gasps ]

18:21.500 --> 18:24.367
- Stop, Homer!
- [ Gasps ]

18:24.470 --> 18:29.134
By smashing my chair,
you're only hurting yourself.

18:29.241 --> 18:30.799
[ Growls ]

18:30.909 --> 18:34.106
[ Yelping, Grunts ]

18:36.448 --> 18:38.780
I'll get you, you fat lunatic!

18:38.884 --> 18:42.376
- [ Tires Screeching ]
- Uh-oh.

18:42.488 --> 18:44.752
[ Whimpering ]

18:51.430 --> 18:53.330
[ Panting ]

18:53.432 --> 18:56.333
All right! The museum's still open.

18:56.435 --> 18:59.302
- Why don't you like Edison that much?
- [ Grunts ]

19:01.240 --> 19:04.676
- Hey, folks. Do you like riddles?
- [ Chattering ]

19:04.776 --> 19:06.767
Okay, then.

19:06.879 --> 19:10.906
How many geniuses does it take
to invent a lightbulb?

19:12.518 --> 19:15.043
Just one: Thomas Edison.

19:15.154 --> 19:19.682
- [ Laughter, Applause ]
- That's very good.

19:19.791 --> 19:21.691
And that's true too.
It's funny and true.

19:21.793 --> 19:26.958
Now behind that door is
Edison's actual preserved brain.

19:27.065 --> 19:28.794
[ Gasping ]

19:28.901 --> 19:32.667
Ordinarily, folks, tour groups are not
allowed to see it...

19:32.771 --> 19:36.707
- and, of course, today will be no exception.
- [ Groaning ]

19:36.808 --> 19:41.245
Now no tour would be complete without
a visit to Edison's boyhood gift shop.

19:41.346 --> 19:44.804
[ Chattering ]

19:48.687 --> 19:51.622
<i>[ Chattering Continues ]</i>

20:00.666 --> 20:02.861
Now let's take care of business.

20:05.637 --> 20:07.537
Out of the way.

20:07.639 --> 20:10.733
This is one invention you're not
getting credit for, you inspiration hog.

20:10.842 --> 20:12.639
Your electric hammer, maestro?

20:14.379 --> 20:18.372
Invent your way
out of this, Edison! Hmm?

20:20.419 --> 20:22.319
<i>Hmm.</i>

20:25.557 --> 20:30.290
<i>[ Gasps ] Look, Son.
Edison was just like me.</i>

20:30.395 --> 20:31.953
You mean the wild mood swings?

20:32.064 --> 20:36.364
No! We both lived
in another man's shadow.

20:36.468 --> 20:41.963
This old-timey nerd and I have suffered
the same frustration and heartache.

20:42.074 --> 20:44.008
We're not rivals.

20:44.109 --> 20:48.443
We're just a couple of dreamers
who set the bar a little too high.

20:50.015 --> 20:53.143
- I can't destroy your work, my friend.
- Can I?

20:53.252 --> 20:57.621
No, but we'll stop off at the da Vinci museum
on the way home.

20:57.723 --> 20:59.850
Uh, I think that's in Italy, Dad.

20:59.958 --> 21:02.085
Oh. Well, then we'll take it out
on Eli Whitney.

21:02.194 --> 21:04.822
<i>Authorities say the phony pope...</i>

21:04.930 --> 21:10.459
can be recognized by his high-top sneakers
and incredibly foul mouth.

21:10.569 --> 21:13.470
In other news, Thomas Edison,
the greatest inventor of all time-

21:13.572 --> 21:15.904
- [ Both Gasp ]
- is apparently still inventing...

21:16.008 --> 21:18.442
despite the notable handicap
of being dead.

21:18.543 --> 21:20.135
That's my Tommy!

21:20.245 --> 21:23.874
[ Brockman ] Two new Edison creations
have just been discovered in his museum.

21:23.982 --> 21:27.418
- A six-legged chair that won't tip over-
- [ Applause ]

21:27.519 --> 21:30.113
and even more astounding,
an electric hammer.

21:30.222 --> 21:33.316
<i>- [ Applause ]
- [ Camera Shutters Clicking ]</i>

21:33.425 --> 21:35.791
That was your idea.

21:35.894 --> 21:39.125
This brilliant innovation is
expected to generate millions...

21:39.231 --> 21:41.927
- for Edison's already-wealthy heirs.
- [ Laughing ]

21:42.034 --> 21:44.059
Dad, those should be your millions.

21:44.169 --> 21:46.967
I gotta admit, Homer.
You're takin' this pretty well.

21:47.072 --> 21:51.736
Let's just say
I'm sitting in the right chair.

22:38.557 --> 22:40.525
- [ Murmuring ]
- Shh!

